race.description: Gippsland Cancer Care Centre Cup Hcp (56)
race.comment: PALACE WINTER (3) peaks and has been threatening another win. He's been kept on the fresh side and kept up to the mark with a jumpout. He races forward, and his Mornington effort last time stacks right up. VAN GERWEN (2) showed enough over this distance range last preparation to say this is winnable putting his best foot forward. He was in the market and didn't have the best of it early stepping up to this trip at Kilmore second up and will race forward again from a handier gate. Tipping improvement. WOMEN IN UNIFORM (5) found a distant place here over a staying trip but was much better beaten a whisker over 2200m at Bairnsdale prior. Has the rail and the 3kg claim brings her into it again. AMAWASHA (1) resumes and immediately kicks off over a middle distance journey. Fitness the query but has trialled three times in readiness.
